The Windows installer provides command line parameters for unattended installation:


/h: display help regarding the command line parameters;

/S: run setup in silent mode;

/server=url1,url2: set the server(s) URL(s);

/tag=tagname: set an agent tag;

/user=username: set a user name;

/pass=password: set a password;

/realm=realm: set a realm;

/ca-cert-file=filename: set an SSL certificate;

/no-ssl-check: disable SSL certificate checking when establishing HTTPS connections;

/proxy=http://proxy/: set an HTTP proxy;

/debug: enable the debug mode;

/rpc-trust-localhost: allow the local user to wake the agent up;

/scan-homedirs: look for virtual machines in users' home directories;

/runnow: start an inventory at the end of the installation.
